This paper is about learning to predict efficiently in various settings, including reinforcement learning. The paper discusses algorithms and constructs commonly used in machine learning, such as temporal difference errors and averaging. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
